Step 1: Open CloudWatch

Search AWS Console:

CloudWatch

Open:

Amazon CloudWatch

Step 2: Open Alarms

Left menu:

Alarms

Click:

Create alarm

Step 3: Select metric

Click:

Select metric

Choose:

EC2 → Per-Instance Metrics

Step 4: Select CPUUtilization

Choose your instance:

Example:

i-02506b58f68851ec7

Metric:

CPUUtilization

Click:

Select metric

Step 5: Configure threshold

Choose:

Static

Condition:

Greater than 60

Meaning:

Alarm if CPU > 60%

Step 6: Set evaluation period

Choose:

1 minute

and

1 datapoint

Meaning:

If CPU > 60 for 1 minute → alarm.

Step 7: Create SNS notification

Choose:

Create new topic

Topic name:
cpu-alert-topic

Email:

Enter your email.

SNS means

Amazon Simple Notification Service sends email.

Step 8: Confirm email

AWS sends email.

You must click:

Confirm subscription

Without confirmation alarm cannot send mail.

Step 9: Name alarm

Example:

EC2-CPU-Above-60

Create alarm.

Done

What CloudWatch now does

Every minute:

Checks CPU metric.

If CPU > 60:

Alarm changes state:

OK → ALARM

Then SNS sends email.

Visual alarm states

Test the alarm now

Inside EC2:

yes > /dev/null &

This forces CPU high.

Stop CPU load
pkill yes
